desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.harbour

Class Loading

  • java.lang.Object
    • desmoj.core.simulator.NamedObject
      • desmoj.core.simulator.ModelComponent
        • desmoj.core.advancedModellingFeatures.ProcessCoop
          • desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.harbour.Loading

  • public class Loading
extends ProcessCoop
    Loading is the object representing the process cooperation between a InternalTransporter or Crane process and the Truck or an Internal Transporter he is loading. It is intended that this Loading is used with the WaitQueue construct, where a InernalTransporter or Crane>( as a master process) is waiting for a truck or an internal transporter to load it. During the Loading the master is active and the slaves is passive. The unloading carried out together is described in the method cooperation, which can be overwritten by the user to build more complex models. Until now this method only models the time it takes to load the truck/ an internal transporter.

      • Loading

        public Loading(Model owner,
               java.lang.String name,
               NumericalDist<?> loadTimeStream,
               boolean showInTrace)
        Constructs a Loading process where a master ( InternalTransporter) or Crane is loading slave (Truck or InternalTransporter) in a cooperate process. The time it takes to load the containers (goods) is determined by the specified loadTimeStream.
        Parameters:
        owner - desmoj.Model : The model this Loading is associated to.
        name - java.lang.String : the name of this Loading.
        loadTimeStream - NumericalDist : The random number stream determining the time it takes to load the containers.
        showInTrace - boolean : Flag, if this Loading should produce a trace output or not.

    • Method Detail

      • cooperation

        protected void cooperation(SimProcess master,
                           SimProcess slave)
        This method describes the loading process carried out by the master process (some kind of InternalTransporter or Crane). In this simple case only the time it takes to load the containers (goods) is taken into consideration. If the user building the model has to implement a more complex behavior, he has to overwrite this method in a subclass. The time it takes to load the containers (goods) is obtained from the method getLoadTimeSample().
        Specified by:
        cooperation in class ProcessCoop
        Parameters:
        master - SimProcess : The master process which really loads the cooperation. Should be a subclass of InternalTransporter or Crane.
        slave - SimProcess : The slave process which is lead through the cooperation by the master. Should be a subclass of InternalTransporter or Truck.

      • getLoadTimeSample

        protected SimTime getLoadTimeSample()
        Returns a SimTime object representing the time it takes to load the containers (goods) with the transporter or crane. The time is taken from the given random number stream loadTimeStream.
        Returns:
        desmoj.SimTime : The time it takes to load the containers (goods) with the transporter/crane.
